The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Tuesday, December 10, 2002 				 Bengal IT funds hunt
 ALOKANANDA GHOSH																								Calcutta, Dec. 9: With IT-enabled services bringing in immense employment opportunities, the Bengal government is making the right moves to attract clients to the state. 																								A 50-member business delegation led by the Confederation of Indian Industry will visit European countries and the US to interact with customers in those countries. Government officials and players in the IT-enabled services sector will be part of the team. Says V. V. R. Babu, chief information officer of ITC Ltd, The idea is to provide a platform for companies to get in touch with customers overseas. 
